data.title: Ingrid Bergman's grandson Roberto Rossellini shows off his model looks at Bulgari event.
data.meta_description: Isabella Rossellini's son Roberto Rossellini has grown into a handsome young man who certainly looks dashing in a suit. And on Wednesday evening he showed off his good looks.
data.text:
Isabella Rossellini's son Roberto Rossellini has grown into a handsome young man who certainly looks dashing in a suit.

And on Wednesday evening the budding model, 28, showed off his natural good looks as he attended the Bulgari event in New York City with Irina Shayk and Dove Cameron.

The Blue Velvet actress adopted Roberto in 1993 when she was engaged to English actor Gary Oldman.

Isabella also has a daughter named Elettra Rossellini Wiedemann, 38, who also works as a model.

Roberto stood out at the Bulgari event with a crisp white shirt and no tie as he had on a dark suit. There was a white gold necklace with a diamond pendant around his neck. And he wore his hair in thin dreadlocks.

Roberto has done well as a runway model as he has worked for Dolce & Gabbana and Michael Kors. He is also interested in photography.

The star has been dating filmmaker Kai Marie for the past seven years.

Isabella - born Isabella Fiorella Elettra Giovanna Rossellini in Rome, Italy - started her career as a fashion model for Vogue then went into acting with her most famous role being Blue Velvet.

The brunette beauty, 69, also popped up in 1990's Wild At Heart with Laura Dern and 1992's Death Becomes Her with Meryl Streep.

And the cover girl has also had some very famous romances.

Isabella was wed to director Martin Scorsese of GoodFellas and Gangs Of New York fame from 1979 until 1982.

Then she was married to Jonathan Wiedeman from 1983 until 1986.

The star also dated director David Lynch (1986–1991) and was engaged to actor Gary Oldman (1994–1996).

Isabella's parents are even more famous than she is: her mother is the late Hollywood Golden Age icon Ingrid Bergman and her father is the late film director Roberto Rossellini (two of his biggest films are Stromboli and Paisan).

Ingrid was born in Sweden and took Hollywood by storm with her great looks and screen charisma.

Her most famous movie is 1942's epic romance Casablanca with Humphrey Bogart set during WWII. It is considered one of the best movies of all time.

But she also showed up in the thrilling 1946 spy movie Notorious with Cary Grant and 1944's noir mystery Gaslight with Charles Boyer.

In 2017 Roberto talked about becoming a model to Coveteur.

'I thought modeling was something I could maybe do at some point, but I never thought it would be the thing I'm doing now,' said the star.

'It started with me randomly getting scouted in New York City by a photographer, and she wanted me to model for L'Officiel Italia. It was funny because right after I was done shooting, my mom came up to me and was like, "Well, you just got scouted randomly. Why don't you just go ahead and actually model?"

'I got in touch with Ford and ended up getting signed a week later. I started working in June. It's fun—I'm really enjoying it.'

His mom Isabella thought modeling would be a good way for him to network and learn more about the fashion industry and photography as well.

'It feels like I'm learning a little bit about everything—clothing, photography, how to be in front of a camera and behind it,' he offered.

As far as coming from an acting dynasty, he does not want to use Isabella's and Ingrid's names to get by: 'Personally, I don't want people to just see me as a celebrity kid. I understand it's cool and a blessing—I love my mom for who she is and all that—but I feel like it has a lot to do with my own personality and what I do,' said Roberto.

'I'm trying to make a mark for myself. I'm just a regular guy who is creative, an artist and now a model. It's just another thing to throw onto the plate.'

And he wants to use modeling as a platform for people to understand who he is.

'More than just a celebrity kid, more than just Isabella Rossellini's son,' he shared. 'I want people to understand that I'm Roberto, and I'm actually a cool person. It's interesting that I'm labeled like that, but at the same time, I step away from that as much as I can.'
